    "updated_at": "2018-10-24T10:56:40Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Instead of pausing any queues this can simply be implemented as the ability to queue a unit at the top of the stack (after the currently produced unit). \r\n\r\nFor example starting with this stack:\r\n```\r\n# In progress:\r\nE1\r\n# Queued:\r\nE1, E1, E3, E1, E1, E3, etc.\r\n```\r\nThe player uses a modifier, say `Alt + click`, to insert a unit at the beginning of the queue resulting in this stack:\r\n```\r\n# Still in progress:\r\nE1\r\n# Queued:\r\nE6, E1, E1, E3, E1, E1, E3, etc.\r\n```\r\nIf the player wishes to start construction of the inserted unit right away, they should manually cancel the \"in progress\" unit. "
  },
