    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is proposing a fundamental change in the classic production logic - one of the defining features of the production logic is the choice between throwing away production time (when cancelling a unit) vs getting a more appropriate unit out slightly sooner.  This would also introduce strategies such as pausing production for many items at 99%, and then releasing them all at once when someone attacks you / you capture an enemy facility / etc.\r\n\r\n I wouldn't object to merging a support for this (like we did for KKND's `ParallelProductionQueue`), but I would object to adopting it in our default mods (like I did for KKND's `ParallelProductionQueue`)."
  },
