    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@pchote What I'm suggesting is not a fundamental change. It's only a modifier for pushing an item to the top of the queue - **after** the currently produced item and **without** pausing anything. This is not a fundamental change but a time-saver and a usability improvement. And as others have pointed out this would make specialty units (engies, spies, hijackers, etc.) used more often as you would not have to cancel your whole queue just to train a single E6.\r\n\r\n@matjaeck The production UI is a whole other question that IMO deserves a separate ticket. Right now it's not very user friendly as the production commands and shortcuts are not exposed to the UI."
  },
